Class AssertionImpl

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyc.kb.client.KbObjectImpl<T>
      • com.cyc.kb.client.AssertionImpl
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.Assertion, com.cyc.kb.KbObject, com.cyc.kb.KbObject.KbObjectWithArity
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    FactImpl, RuleImpl

    public class AssertionImpl
extends KbObjectImpl<T>
implements com.cyc.kb.Assertion
    An Assertion object is a facade for a #$CycLAssertion in Cyc KB. An assertion is a semantically well formed Sentence, in a specific Context.

    Sub-classes include Fact and Rule.

    Since:
    1.0

    $Id: AssertionImpl.java 176349 2017-12-19 01:38:11Z nwinant $

      • retriggerForwardInference

        public com.cyc.kb.Assertion retriggerForwardInference()
                                               throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbException
        Retrigger forward inference against this assertion. In general when adding or removing assertions, Cyc's truth-maintenance system automatically handles this, but there are exceptional cases (e.g. where resource constraints prevented forward inference from running exhaustively) where it needs to be done manually. This is also known as repropagating the assertion.
        Returns:
        the assertion that had its forward inference retriggered.
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbException

      • replaceTerms

        protected <O> O replaceTerms(Map substitutions)
                      throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException,
                             com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
        Replace non-destructively a set of objects with another set of objects, in a Non-Atomic Term or a Sentence. Replacement is not supported within Assertions, Atomic Terms, Variables and Symbols. Although, set of objects replaced can be any KBObject or Java primitive object.
        Type Parameters:
        O -
        Parameters:
        substitutions - the replacement mapping
        Returns:
        A new object with the substitutions made in the original object
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
